Installs the PostgreSQL database management system on your Ubuntu system.

	1)sudo apt install postgresql
	

Checks the status of the PostgreSQL service to ensure it is running correctly.
	2)sudo systemctl status postgresql.service:

Switches to the PostgreSQL user account (postgres) to perform administrative tasks.

	3)sudo -i -u postgres:
	
Opens the PostgreSQL command-line interface, allowing you to interact with the PostgreSQL database system.

	4)psql:

Creates a new PostgreSQL database named "demo."

	5)create database (databaseName):

Lists all available databases, including the newly created "demo."

	6)\l (within psql):

